
Berkeley, 30 Jan. 1781. The terms of enlistment of the men in his regiment will expire in ten months, most of whom can be enlisted for the duration of the war for a bounty of one third or perhaps less what is now given. The men can best be reenlisted now; When they are Clear or nearly so of the Service it will be with great Difficulty and at a great expence they will be inlisted. If a sum of money can be sent with the bearer, Major Hunter, between one and two Hundred good men may Certainly be got for the war.
